# UiType & field-type system

## Two distinct type resolutions — never conflate them

| Method | Owner | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Field::getUiTypeName(): string` | `src/Modules/Base/Models/Field.php` | Semantic type for business logic: import, workflow, reports, query conditions. Uses `SEMANTIC_TYPE_MAP`. |
| `Field::getFieldDataType()` | same — alias for `getUiTypeName()` | Kept for backward compatibility. **No return-type annotation** (see pitfall below). |
| `WebserviceField::getFieldDataType()` | `src/Webservices/WebserviceField.php` | REST API type from `vtiger_ws_fieldtype` + `typeofdata` fallback. `V~O` → `'string'` is correct for the API but **wrong for UI**. Never use as a UI fallback. |
| `BaseUiType::getInstanceFromField()` | `src/Modules/Base/UiTypes/BaseUiType.php` | Picks the renderer class via `UITYPE_CLASS_MAP` (uitype int → class suffix). **Does not call `getFieldDataType()`** for known uitypes — fully independent of the webservice layer. |

