## SEMANTIC_TYPE_MAP — business logic type (Field)

Located at `Field::SEMANTIC_TYPE_MAP`. Maps uitype integer to the semantic string used by import, workflow, reports, and query conditions.

Key entries that differ from the naive uitype name:

| uitype | Semantic type | Why it matters |
|---|---|---|
| 3 | `autogenerated` | Not `recordNumber` — uitype 4 is `recordNumber` |
| 15 | `picklist` | Role-based single select |
| 16, 33 | `multipicklist` | 33 = LayoutEditor `MultiSelectCombo`; **must** match `UITYPE_CLASS_MAP` |
| 26 | `documentsFolder` | Not `reference` |
| 27 | `fileLocationType` | |
| 54 | `multiowner` | Not `owner` |
| 61 | `file` | Not `image` |
| 69 | `image` | Not `file` |
| 117 | `currencyList` | Not `currency` (71/72 are `currency`) |
| 305 | `multiReferenceValue` | Auto-aggregated from relations; read-only on Edit |
| 306 | `MultiReference` | Manual multi-pick via popup; comma-separated CRM IDs in TEXT; target module from `vtiger_fieldmodulerel` (implements `ReferenceListProvider`) |
| *(unmapped)* | delegated to `WebserviceField::getFieldDataType()` | Falls back to `vtiger_ws_fieldtype`; plain text fields get `'string'` via `typeofdata V~O` |

### MultiReference (306) — Edit UI

Looks like Multipicklist (`email_template_type`): Select2 `select2-selection--multiple` chips; click empty area → record popup (not a dropdown of all records).

| Piece | Location |
|---|---|
| Template | `layouts/basic/modules/Base/uitypes/MultiReference.tpl` |
| JS | `public/layouts/basic/modules/Base/resources/Edit.js` → `registerMultiReferenceFields()` (+ minify) |
| UiType | `src/Modules/Base/UiTypes/MultiReference.php` |
| QueryField | `src/QueryField/MultiReferenceField.php` |

- Hidden `input.sourceField[data-fieldtype="multiReference"][data-multiple="true"]` holds comma-separated IDs for save; `<select multiple class="chzn-select js-multi-reference-select">` has **no** `name` — options only for currently selected records.
- **Smarty:** write `multiple class="..."` on one line; a line break between `multiple` and `class` compiles to invalid `multipleclass=`.
- **Init order:** `app.changeSelectElementView()` runs on `document.ready` before `registerMultiReferenceFields()` — destroy existing Select2 and reinit with `tags: false`, `minimumResultsForSearch: Infinity`. Popup via `select2:opening` (preventDefault) + `openPopUp`; selection event `Vtiger.MultiReference.Selection`.
- **Remove chip (×):** mousedown on `.select2-selection__choice__remove` sets Select2 `unselecting` flag (same as `app.js`) so `select2:opening` / search-field focus do not reopen the popup.

