## Template methods on UiType classes

| Method | Default (BaseUiType) | Used by |
|---|---|---|
| `getTemplateName()` | `uitypes/String.tpl` | EditView, QuickCreate |
| `getDetailViewTemplateName()` | `uitypes/StringDetailView.tpl` | DetailView |
| `getListSearchTemplateName()` | `uitypes/FieldSearchView.tpl` | ListView search row |

Templates live in `layouts/basic/modules/Base/uitypes/` (Base) or `layouts/basic/modules/<Module>/uitypes/` (override).
Compiled cache: `cache/templates_c/basic/` — clear with `rm -f cache/templates_c/basic/*.php` after template changes.

### ListView date range search — datetime needs the Date search template
The range date-picker on the list search row is wired in JS only to inputs with class `.dateField` + `data-calendar-type="range"`, which **only** `uitypes/DateFieldSearchView.tpl` emits (`ListSearch.js` → `registerDateListSearch()`, `mode: 'range'`). `Datetime` (uitype 70, e.g. `createdtime`) must override `getListSearchTemplateName()` to return `'uitypes/DateFieldSearchView.tpl'` — otherwise it falls back to the plain `FieldSearchView.tpl` text input (no calendar). `ListSearch.js` sends operator `bw` for both `date` and `datetime`. Picker has no OK button: value updates live on each day click; search fires on picker close (`DatePicker.onHide`) when `AUTO_REFRESH_RECORD_LIST_ON_SELECT_CHANGE` is on, or on **Enter** (document handler in `registerDateListSearchEnterKey()` — see `listview-javascript-playbook.mdc`).

### `operatorBw` with a single date = whole day
`bw` ("between") splits the value on `,`. A single date (e.g. from a URL/API `["createdtime","bw","2026-06-11"]`) leaves `$value[1]` null → empty upper bound → `BETWEEN` matches nothing. `DateField`/`DatetimeField::operatorBw()` fall back `$end` to `$value[0]` so one date covers that full day (`00:00:00`–`23:59:59` for datetime).

