## Pitfalls

### Adding `: string` to `getFieldDataType()` causes a fatal error
`Field::getFieldDataType()` is overridden (without a return type) by 6 subclasses:
- `src/Modules/Calendar/Models/Field.php`
- `src/Modules/Users/Models/Field.php`
- `src/Modules/Settings/SMSNotifier/Models/Field.php`
- `src/Modules/Settings/MappedFields/Models/Field.php`
- `src/Modules/Settings/Leads/Models/Field.php`
- `src/Modules/Base/InventoryFields/Basic.php`

Use `getUiTypeName(): string` (which has a return type) when you need a typed call.

### Reference fields on DetailView — modal edit, not in-place
- **Gate:** `Field::isReferenceModalEditable()` (`datatype === reference`, `isEditable()`, `displaytype !== 10`). Separate from `isAjaxEditable()` (which still blocks uitype 10/51/59 for in-place).
- **Save contract:** same as other inline edits — `SaveAjax` with `field` + `value` (CRM id); `Reference::getDBValue()` normalizes empty → `0`; response `display_value` is HTML link.
- **Do not** render hidden `.edit` + `Reference.tpl` in DetailView cells — use modal (`ReferenceEditModal`) only.

### uitype 33 — renderer and semantic type must both be multipicklist
LayoutEditor creates `MultiSelectCombo` as uitype **33** (`Settings/LayoutEditor/Models/Module.php`). If `UITYPE_CLASS_MAP` or `SEMANTIC_TYPE_MAP` treats 33 as single `picklist`:
- DetailView shows raw ` \|##\|` delimiters instead of comma-separated labels
- DetailView inline edit finds hidden `name="field"` instead of `select[name="field[]"]` (`Detail.js` only appends `[]` when `data-type="multipicklist"`)
- `SaveAjax` skips `implode(' \|##\| ', …)` for array values

Both maps: **33 → `Multipicklist` / `multipicklist`**. uitype 33 is still **role-based** (`Field::isRoleBased()`). Example fields: `ProjektyRekrutacyjne.benefits`, `project_publishing_lang`.

### `WebserviceField` as a UI fallback silently breaks picklists
`typeofdata = V~O` maps to `'string'` in `WebserviceField`. If `SEMANTIC_TYPE_MAP` is missing an entry and falls through to `WebserviceField`, a picklist field gets type `'string'`, which causes `getInstanceFromField()` to use `StringType` → `String.tpl` → labels display as raw `PLL_*` keys instead of translated text.

### Stale per-request cache
`Field::$fieldDataType` is a per-instance property cache. It is set once and never invalidated within the same request. If a field model is reused with different context (e.g. same object, different module), the cached type from the first resolution persists. Do not reuse field model instances across modules.
